  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5799",
  "title": "Algolia requires invalid router in next js 13 app directory",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nThe latest version of next.js 13 and algolia react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs is incompatible because it requires that you import a router that only works with the old pages directory. To my understanding, nextjs uses { useRouter } from \"next/navigation\" when you need a router in a client component. Can you please recommend a fix to this issue? I would really appreciate any help.\r\n\r\n\"use client\";\r\nimport { SingletonRouter } from \"next/router\";\r\nimport { createInstantSearchRouterNext } from \"react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs\";\r\n\r\n<InstantSearch  indexName=\"products\" searchClient={searchClient}  routing={{ router: createInstantSearchRouterNext({           singletonRouter })}}>\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Use the latest next.js 13\r\n2. Add reactinstantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs\r\n3. Try to use this on a \"use client\" page or normal \"server\" page in the new \"app\" directory.\r\n4. You'll get an error saying that next/router can't be used on anything other than a client page.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nWork with { useRouter } or any other router option in the app directory of next js 13.\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs 6.4.73\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
